Banned in the U.S.A. and was marketed as Luther Campbell's debut album, though there were only minor changes to the track listing, notably, remixes to "Banned in the U.S.A. and "Mama Juanita". It managed to make it to #21 on the Billboard 200 and #10 on the Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums.
